&nbsp; "Green and Left Alliance in agreement with Roberto Salis > has decided to nominate his daughter Ilaria, held in Hungary, under conditions that severely violate the rights of people, in their lists at the next European elections". Nicola Fratoianni> and Angelo Bonelli> of the Green Left Alliance.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"In these hours - Fratoianni and Bonelli explain - the national executive groups are discussing the methods of this choice that wants to protect the rights and dignity of a European citizen, also from the inertia of the Italian authorities in order to obtain rapid scarceness in favor of the domicile arrests denied with the last decision by the Hungarian judges".
&nbsp;
The idea is that around the candidacy of Ilaria Salis "we can generate - the two members of Avs continue - a great and generous battle so that the European Union defends the principles of the rule of law and reaffirms the inviolability of fundamental human rights throughout its territory and in each of the Member States. Ours is a gesture that can serve to denounce uncivilized methods of detention, especially to those who are still waiting for a judgment." "In this way Europe Green and Italian Left intend to bring in the future European Parliament - conclude - legislative initiatives for the protection of the rights of persons involved in criminal proceedings in all countries of the Union. A press conference will be convened in the next few days."

