AGI -&nbsp;The Agreement on Migrants is worth overcoming the old Dublin Agreement and indicating a model of cooperation at European level. Sergio Mattarella praises the Covenant on the right of asylum, approved by the European Parliament and now to the examination of the EU Council, which sends in the attic the Dublin regulation, which he himself defined several times "prehistoric". >
&nbsp;
Despite the criticisms made by Pd, M5s and Lega, the head of the state, from the eastern border of Bulgaria>, expresses its satisfaction, during the meeting with the homologue Rumen Radev, for "an understanding that will exceed the one now dated and completely current in Dublin of so long back and opens the door to a more intense collaboration in the Union to govern a growing phenomenon that requires being faced by the Union as such". Net of the distinctions that have arisen from the extreme wings, Mattarella returns on a leitmotiv: "the phenomenon of migration can be ruled > with order and not in an uncomposed and disorderly manner, as happens today, if the task is assumed by the EU".
<br As for the future of the Union, for the head of the State, it will have to "understand important choices to become increasingly cohesive and capable of playing a leading role in the world". A new test will be the competitiveness plan, developed by Mario Draghi and the 27: "In the European Council of the next few hours we talk about important topics such as competitiveness in the Union, an element which allows, by developing it adequately, to offer greater opportunities and opportunities for the future of our young people."
&nbsp;
But with Radev, with whom tomorrow Mattarella will visit the Italian contingent of the base of Novo Selo that covers the eastern front of NATO > across the Black Sea, the head of the State also reiterated the support common to Ukraine, "to reaffirm the principle of equal dignity of every State and that it is not admissible that a larger and stronger state can claim to impose with arms its will &nbsp; to a less powerful state. This subverts the principles of civilization which in the world have grown over the centuries and which have been the basis of the birth of the United Nations in '45. So by reaffirming this and defending Ukraine we reaffirm this principle, of course, we have said together with President Radev, seeking in every way, with great commitment and stubbornness, any possible way to reach the end of the conflict and a just peace."
<br But as he pointed out two days ago talking about the future of NATO, now the outbreak of crisis has invested the Middle East, it is necessary to preside also the south-eastern side and "the risk that widens the conflict is dramatically present, it must be made every effort for a solution and the only possible is two states for two peoples". With the common framework of EU and NATO, which guarantees "a common effort of security and peace together", Italy and Bulgaria collaborate on different fronts, so that "the exchange goes towards 7 billion in the past year and we hope to grow".
&nbsp;
<
<div </div
</div
&nbsp;
"I have expressed our satisfaction to President Radev for the decision of the European Union to finally erase restrictions on air and naval traffic to those coming from Bulgaria. We hope that this will soon be done also for the terrestrial borders, because &nbsp; a complete entry into the Schengen Area, which is one of the elements that mark the life of our Union" the head of the State noted, for which a rapid entry in the Eurozone is desirable.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
